DATASET DESCRIPTION

This dataset contains detailed statistics for football matches in the English Premier League from 2010 to 2020.

Each row represents a single match, including both home and away team performance metrics, 
as well as the final match outcome. The dataset enables comprehensive analysis of team performance, match dynamics, and statistical trends across seasons.


GENERAL INFORMATION

X --> Unique identifier for each match

season --> Season in which the match was played

date
Date of the match

home_team
Name of the home team

away_team
Name of the away team


HOME TEAM STATISTICS

home_clearances
Number of clearances made by the home team

home_corners
Number of corner kicks

home_fouls_conceded
Number of fouls committed

home_offsides
Number of offsides

home_passes
Total number of passes made

home_possession
Ball possession percentage

home_red_cards
Number of red cards received

home_shots
Total number of shots

home_shots_on_target
Number of shots on target

home_tackles
Number of tackles made

home_touches
Total number of touches

home_yellow_cards
Number of yellow cards received


AWAY TEAM STATISTICS

away_clearances
Number of clearances made by the away team

away_corners
Number of corner kicks

away_fouls_conceded
Number of fouls committed

away_offsides
Number of offsides

away_passes
Total number of passes made

away_possession
Ball possession percentage

away_red_cards
Number of red cards received

away_shots
Total number of shots

away_shots_on_target
Number of shots on target

away_tackles
Number of tackles made

away_touches
Total number of touches

away_yellow_cards
Number of yellow cards received


MATCH OUTCOME

goal_home_ft
Full-time goals scored by the home team

goal_away_ft
Full-time goals scored by the away team

sg_match_ft
Goal difference (home team goals minus away team goals)

result
Final match result (Home Win, Draw, Away Win)


NOTES

- The dataset includes both offensive and defensive metrics for each team.
- Possession values are expressed as percentages.
- The dataset is suitable for:
  - Performance analysis
  - Statistical exploration
  - SQL-based analytics projects
  - Predictive modeling and machine learning (future extension)
